<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 02 at 5:11PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Pittsburg County through 545 PM CDT...
At 510 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
northwest of Haywood. This storm was drifting southeast.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Haywood...
Arpelar...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
